> *« Il est vrai que M. Fourier avait l'opinion que le but principal des mathématiques était l'utilité publique et l'explication des phénomènes naturels ; mais un philosophe comme lui aurait dû savoir que le but unique de la science, c'est l'honneur de l'esprit humain. »*
> 
> — **Carl Gustav Jacob Jacobi**, Letter to Adrien-Marie Legendre, 1830

> *"The unexamined experiment is not worth running."* — **Socrates** (paraphrased)

The **SocrateAI Scientific Agora** is a state-of-the-art neuro-symbolic, frugal AI framework designed by the **Socrate AI Lab** (Paris, France). It orchestrates autonomous scientific agents to discover, simulate, verify, and catalog complex scientific and industrial solutions—all within strict cost constraints ($100 per experiment ceiling, $500 project budget). 

Agora replaces computational brute-force with mathematical elegance, marrying **dialectical Socratic orchestration** (Socrates) with **highly-innovative mathematical conics** (Galois), **rigid formal theorem verification** (Euler), **empirical physical solvers** (Galileo), **computational cost & resource optimization** (Turing), and **cryptographic vault memory cataloging** (Hypatie).

